description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in working as a Health Care Assistant within the operating theatres at Broomfield Hospital in ENT,Maxillofacial,Head &amp; Neck,Gnaecology &amp; Obstetrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a modern theatre unit across Mid Essex, with state of the art technology. Our friendly, dedicated and highly skilled team demand the very best care for patients at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be working under the direction of our registered theatre staff undertaking duties relating to the care of patients including the preparation and cleaning of the theatres.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are lots of opportunities to develop your skills with our competency package and in house training which is open to all of our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To join our team you must be hard working, have attention to detail, be caring, compassionate and keen to learn. In return we offer you a really satisfying and rewarding role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJudith HaddowJob titleTheatre Lead PractitionerEmail addressJudith.Haddow@meht.nhs.ukTelephone number01245-494577Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
